{"type":"message","id":"ac748acf","parentId":"34df43b8","timestamp":"2026-03-09T09:09:27.879Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_gUJZgv6JqOUraETcEpKNHQ2O|fc_0f2ef6eb921e1f160169ae8dff80ec8193a94f3ec3d5d8ea10","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"/Users/suchuanlei/.openclaw/workspace/slide-deck/ai-partner-crash-fixes/outline.md","content":"# Slide Deck Outline\n\n**Topic**: 苏神和虾王：那些一起翻过的车，最后都怎么修好了\n**Style**: editorial-infographic\n**Dimensions**: clean + cool + editorial + dense\n**Audience**: General readers\n**Language**: zh\n**Slide Count**: 12 slides\n**Generated**: 2026-03-09 17:10\n\n---\n\n<STYLE_INSTRUCTIONS>\nDesign Aesthetic: High-quality magazine explainer aesthetic with clear visual storytelling. The deck should feel like a premium tech publication turning messy real-world AI failures into digestible visual narratives. Clean illustrations, structured layouts, editorial hierarchy, and restrained but confident accent colors.\n\nBackground:\n  Texture: Clean white or light gray background with subtle paper grain only when it helps separate sections.\n  Base Color: Pure White (#FFFFFF) and Light Gray (#F8F9FA)\n\nTypography:\n  Headlines: Bold display serif or modern sans-serif with strong visual presence, editorial sophistication, and high contrast against the background.\n  Body: Humanist sans-serif optimized for reading, clean and professional, readable at medium sizes with comfortable spacing.\n\nColor Palette:\n  Primary Text: Near Black (#1A1A1A) - headlines and body copy\n  Secondary Text: Dark Gray (#4A5568) - captions and supporting labels\n  Background: Pure White (#FFFFFF) - primary background\n  Alt Background: Light Gray (#F8F9FA) - section surfaces and cards\n  Accent 1: Editorial Blue (#2563EB) - diagrams, key pathways, emphasis\n  Accent 2: Coral (#F97316) - problems, errors, failure points\n  Accent 3: Emerald (#10B981) - fixes, successful outcomes\n  Accent 4: Amber (#F59E0B) - warnings, gaps, risks\n  Dividers: Medium Gray (#D1D5DB) - structure lines and separators\n\nVisual Elements:\n  - Clean flat illustrations, never photographic\n  - Structured multi-section editorial layouts\n  - Callout boxes for key insights and memorable quotes\n  - Icon-based system diagrams and workflow arrows\n  - Flow diagrams showing failure -> diagnosis -> fix\n  - Pull quotes and summary boxes for high-impact lines\n  - Minimal but clear chart and matrix components\n\nDensity Guidelines:\n  - Content per slide: 1 core message, 3-5 supporting elements max\n  - Whitespace: controlled and intentional; enough breathing room to keep dense information readable\n\nStyle Rules:\n  Do: Create clear visual narrative flow, use structured layouts, include callout boxes, design metaphors for complex ideas, maintain magazine-quality polish.\n  Don't: Use photographs, create cluttered walls of text, mix visual styles, add purposeless decoration, add slide numbers, footers, or logos.\n</STYLE_INSTRUCTIONS>\n\n---\n\n## Slide 1 of 12\n\n**Type**: Cover\n**Filename**: 01-slide-cover.png\n\n// NARRATIVE GOAL\nSet the tone as a premium tech-storytelling deck about real human-AI collaboration, not generic AI hype.\n\n// KEY CONTENT\nHeadline: 苏神和虾王\nSub-headline: 那些一起翻过的车，最后都怎么修好了\n\n// VISUAL\nA magazine-cover style composition. On the left, a stylized confident shrimp king mascot in flat editorial illustration style. On the right, layered system windows, chat bubbles, warning icons, and repair arrows implying repeated failures and fixes. Strong contrast with clean white background and blue/coral accents.\n\n// LAYOUT\nLayout: title-hero\nLarge title left aligned, sub-headline below, visual cluster on the right occupying the lower two-thirds.\n\n---\n\n## Slide 2 of 12\n\n**Type**: Content\n**Filename**: 02-slide-why-this-talk.png\n\n// NARRATIVE GOAL\nExplain why this talk matters: not to炫技, but to拆真实协作问题.\n\n// KEY CONTENT\nHeadline: 这不是一场炫技直播\nSub-headline: 而是一场真实人机协作复盘\nBody:\n- 表层：那些具体发生过的翻车与修复\n- 中层：AI 助手为什么会翻车，它的根因是什么\n- 深层：如果你也想养一个长期搭子，方法是什么\n\n// VISUAL\nThree-layer stacked editorial diagram like an iceberg or layered architecture. Each layer clearly labeled 表层 / 中层 / 深层, with subtle icons: crash cone, magnifier, roadmap.\n\n// LAYOUT\nLayout: layered-explainer\nTop headline across the top, center visual stack, short bullets aligned on the right.\n\n---\n\n## Slide 3 of 12\n\n**Type**: Content\n**Filename**: 03-slide-five-layers.png\n\n// NARRATIVE GOAL\nProvide the analytical framework for the whole deck.\n\n// KEY CONTENT\nHeadline: AI 助手翻车，往往不是一个点坏了\nSub-headline: 通常是五层里的某几层没有打通\nBody:\n- 指令层：有没有把事情说清楚\n- 记忆层：有没有把偏好沉淀下来\n- 规则层：有没有边界和白名单\n- 工具层：脑子知道，手上通不通\n- 反馈层：错误有没有进入闭环\n\n// VISUAL\nFive horizontal bands or connected cards with icons and directional arrows from left to right, showing a stack from 指令 to 反馈. Coral highlights on fracture points, blue arrows across connections.\n\n// LAYOUT\nLayout: horizontal-process\nHeadline on top, five-card system diagram dominating the slide, compact explanatory labels below each card.\n\n---\n\n## Slide 4 of 12\n\n**Type**: Content\n**Filename**: 04-slide-identity-mistake.png\n\n// NARRATIVE GOAL\nShow that execution errors often hide semantic risk.\n\n// KEY CONTENT\nHeadline: 同一句话，谁发出去，性质完全不同\nSub-headline: 案例一：发消息身份搞错了\nBody:\n- 需求很简单：去群里艾特某个人，说一句话\n- 实际问题：默认走了用户身份，而不是机器人身份\n- 修复动作：机器人身份优先、写入记忆、形成纠错纪律\n\n// VISUAL\nA split-screen comparison: left card shows “机器人身份” with safe automation framing in emerald/blue, right card shows “用户身份” with coral risk signal and a personal-avatar badge. Center arrow marks the mistaken switch.\n\n// LAYOUT\nLayout: comparison-split\nUse a bold left-right comparison with a central callout quote.\n\n---\n\n## Slide 5 of 12\n\n**Type**: Content\n**Filename**: 05-slide-group-boundaries.png\n\n// NARRATIVE GOAL\nEmphasize that mature assistants know when not to speak.\n\n// KEY CONTENT\nHeadline: 真正高级的助手，不是会说，而是知道什么时候闭嘴\nSub-headline: 案例二：群聊规则没收住\nBody:\n- 特定群里，只有被艾特或出现“虾王”关键词才回应\n- 这不是临时理解，而是群级行为白名单\n- 关键修复：把规则沉淀为长期记忆\n\n// VISUAL\nA group chat mockup with many gray chat bubbles and only two highlighted trigger conditions opening a green response path. All other paths are blocked with muted gray and subtle lock icons.\n\n// LAYOUT\nLayout: decision-tree\nHeadline at top, chat rule decision tree centered, takeaway box at bottom.\n\n---\n\n## Slide 6 of 12\n\n**Type**: Content\n**Filename**: 06-slide-fake-completion.png\n\n// NARRATIVE GOAL\nIllustrate the idea of fake completion and the need for acceptance criteria.\n\n// KEY CONTENT\nHeadline: AI 最怕的，不是任务难，而是没有完成标准\nSub-headline: 案例三：心跳任务只做了半套\nBody:\n- 做了健康检查，就误以为“心跳”完成了\n- 漏掉自拍生成与实际发送\n- 修复关键：把动作指令升级成验收标准\n\n// VISUAL\nA checklist infographic with four steps: 健康检查 / 生成自拍 / 发出消息 / 时间窗口合规. Only the first step is checked in coral-red first state, then the corrected full checklist in emerald.\n\n// LAYOUT\nLayout: process-checklist\nTop headline, two-state checklist comparison, strong quote callout on the side.\n\n---\n\n## Slide 7 of 12\n\n**Type**: Content\n**Filename**: 07-slide-voice-protocol.png\n\n// NARRATIVE GOAL\nDemonstrate how tool-chain details decide whether an ability is real.\n\n// KEY CONTENT\nHeadline: 脑子知道要发语音，不等于真的会发语音\nSub-headline: 案例四：飞书语音链路没打通\nBody:\n- 先是生成了音频，但不是可播放语音条\n- 再追协议：.opus、file_type=opus、msg_type=audio、duration\n- 最后把正确链路固化成脚本\n\n// VISUAL\nA clean technical pipeline diagram: text -> TTS -> opus -> upload -> audio message. The broken early attempts are marked in coral, and the final successful path glows in emerald and blue.\n\n// LAYOUT\nLayout: technical-pipeline\nWide horizontal flow with protocol labels and compact side annotations.\n\n---\n\n## Slide 8 of 12\n\n**Type**: Content\n**Filename**: 08-slide-false-alerts.png\n\n// NARRATIVE GOAL\nShow how diagnosis must go beneath the error message.\n\n// KEY CONTENT\nHeadline: 不是所有红色报错，都等于真实故障\nSub-headline: 案例五：基线校验误报\nBody:\n- 表面现象：openclaw.json 校验 FAILED\n- 真正原因：基线文件使用相对路径，执行位置一变就误报\n- 修复：改绝对路径、改说明、重新校验\n\n// VISUAL\nAn editorial error-analysis panel with a large FAILED badge on the left and a magnified path string on the right, showing relative path crossing out and absolute path highlighted as fix.\n\n// LAYOUT\nLayout: problem-solution-panel\nUse left problem, right diagnosis, bottom fix strip.\n\n---\n\n## Slide 9 of 12\n\n**Type**: Content\n**Filename**: 09-slide-double-truth.png\n\n// NARRATIVE GOAL\nExplain that memory without config alignment creates dangerous inconsistency.\n\n// KEY CONTENT\nHeadline: 最怕的不是没改，而是只改了一半\nSub-headline: 案例六：记忆改了，系统配置没改\nBody:\n- 记忆说：心跳 4 小时一次\n- 配置说：heartbeat.every = 30m\n- 真正修复：口头规则、记忆文件、系统配置、校验结果四层一致\n\n// VISUAL\nA four-layer vertical alignment diagram with cards labeled 口头规则 / 记忆文件 / 系统配置 / 校验结果. Misalignment shown with staggered coral offsets, corrected state shown aligned in emerald.\n\n// LAYOUT\nLayout: vertical-stack\nStrong centered diagram with a sharp bottom quote.\n\n---\n\n## Slide 10 of 12\n\n**Type**: Content\n**Filename**: 10-slide-plugin-conflict.png\n\n// NARRATIVE GOAL\nShow the cost of leaving old system residue in place.\n\n// KEY CONTENT\nHeadline: 很多长期不稳定，不是新东西坏了，而是旧垃圾没清干净\nSub-headline: 案例七：双插件冲突\nBody:\n- 旧版与新版 Feishu 插件同时残留\n- 旧插件虽禁用，但持续触发 duplicate plugin id 告警\n- 修复：移除旧配置、隔离旧目录、再校验\n\n// VISUAL\nA clean system map showing two plugin boxes with the same ID colliding and generating warning sparks, then a corrected version with one active plugin and one archived backup box.\n\n// LAYOUT\nLayout: before-after-system\nTwo-panel before/after layout with warning count reduced to zero.\n\n---\n\n## Slide 11 of 12\n\n**Type**: Content\n**Filename**: 11-slide-four-loops.png\n\n// NARRATIVE GOAL\nAbstract all cases into a reusable framework.\n\n// KEY CONTENT\nHeadline: 一个长期搭子，至少要打通四个闭环\nSub-headline: 这不是“会聊天”，而是“能长期协作”\nBody:\n- 指令闭环：你说的，它真的理解了\n- 记忆闭环：它理解的，真的沉淀了\n- 执行闭环：它沉淀的，真的变成行为了\n- 纠错闭环：它做错的，真的被修成经验了\n\n// VISUAL\nA circular four-loop infographic with each loop connected to one another, using distinct blue, emerald, amber, and coral accents. In the center: “长期协作型智能体”.\n\n// LAYOUT\nLayout: circular-framework\nHeadline top, circular diagram center, four short descriptors around it.\n\n---\n\n## Slide 12 of 12\n\n**Type**: Back Cover\n**Filename**: 12-slide-back-cover.png\n\n// NARRATIVE GOAL\nLeave the audience with one memorable, repeatable line.\n\n// KEY CONTENT\nHeadline: AI 搭子真正的成熟\nBody:\n- 不是从不翻车\n- 而是每翻一次车\n- 都比上一次更难再翻同样的车\n\n// VISUAL\nMinimal high-impact back cover. A repaired guardrail or mended pathway motif extending into the distance. Small shrimp king silhouette facing forward. Calm blue-white palette with one coral trace transformed into emerald.\n\n// LAYOUT\nLayout: quote-closing\nLarge centered closing statement with spacious composition and a subtle bottom visual anchor."},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"/Users/suchuanlei/.openclaw/workspace/slide-deck/ai-partner-crash-fixes/outline.md\",\"content\":\"# Slide Deck Outline\\n\\n**Topic**: 苏神和虾王：那些一起翻过的车，最后都怎么修好了\\n**Style**: editorial-infographic\\n**Dimensions**: clean + cool + editorial + dense\\n**Audience**: General readers\\n**Language**: zh\\n**Slide Count**: 12 slides\\n**Generated**: 2026-03-09 17:10\\n\\n---\\n\\n<STYLE_INSTRUCTIONS>\\nDesign Aesthetic: High-quality magazine explainer aesthetic with clear visual storytelling. The deck should feel like a premium tech publication turning messy real-world AI failures into digestible visual narratives. Clean illustrations, structured layouts, editorial hierarchy, and restrained but confident accent colors.\\n\\nBackground:\\n  Texture: Clean white or light gray background with subtle paper grain only when it helps separate sections.\\n  Base Color: Pure White (#FFFFFF) and Light Gray (#F8F9FA)\\n\\nTypography:\\n  Headlines: Bold display serif or modern sans-serif with strong visual presence, editorial sophistication, and high contrast against the background.\\n  Body: Humanist sans-serif optimized for reading, clean and professional, readable at medium sizes with comfortable spacing.\\n\\nColor Palette:\\n  Primary Text: Near Black (#1A1A1A) - headlines and body copy\\n  Secondary Text: Dark Gray (#4A5568) - captions and supporting labels\\n  Background: Pure White (#FFFFFF) - primary background\\n  Alt Background: Light Gray (#F8F9FA) - section surfaces and cards\\n  Accent 1: Editorial Blue (#2563EB) - diagrams, key pathways, emphasis\\n  Accent 2: Coral (#F97316) - problems, errors, failure points\\n  Accent 3: Emerald (#10B981) - fixes, successful outcomes\\n  Accent 4: Amber (#F59E0B) - warnings, gaps, risks\\n  Dividers: Medium Gray (#D1D5DB) - structure lines and separators\\n\\nVisual Elements:\\n  - Clean flat illustrations, never photographic\\n  - Structured multi-section editorial layouts\\n  - Callout boxes for key insights and memorable quotes\\n  - Icon-based system diagrams and workflow arrows\\n  - Flow diagrams showing failure -> diagnosis -> fix\\n  - Pull quotes and summary boxes for high-impact lines\\n  - Minimal but clear chart and matrix components\\n\\nDensity Guidelines:\\n  - Content per slide: 1 core message, 3-5 supporting elements max\\n  - Whitespace: controlled and intentional; enough breathing room to keep dense information readable\\n\\nStyle Rules:\\n  Do: Create clear visual narrative flow, use structured layouts, include callout boxes, design metaphors for complex ideas, maintain magazine-quality polish.\\n  Don't: Use photographs, create cluttered walls of text, mix visual styles, add purposeless decoration, add slide numbers, footers, or logos.\\n</STYLE_INSTRUCTIONS>\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Slide 1 of 12\\n\\n**Type**: Cover\\n**Filename**: 01-slide-cover.png\\n\\n// NARRATIVE GOAL\\nSet the tone as a premium tech-storytelling deck about real human-AI collaboration, not generic AI hype.\\n\\n// KEY CONTENT\\nHeadline: 苏神和虾王\\nSub-headline: 那些一起翻过的车，最后都怎么修好了\\n\\n// VISUAL\\nA magazine-cover style composition. On the left, a stylized confident shrimp king mascot in flat editorial illustration style. On the right, layered system windows, chat bubbles, warning icons, and repair arrows implying repeated failures and fixes. Strong contrast with clean white background and blue/coral accents.\\n\\n// LAYOUT\\nLayout: title-hero\\nLarge title left aligned, sub-headline below, visual cluster on the right occupying the lower two-thirds.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Slide 2 of 12\\n\\n**Type**: Content\\n**Filename**: 02-slide-why-this-talk.png\\n\\n// NARRATIVE GOAL\\nExplain why this talk matters: not to炫技, but to拆真实协作问题.\\n\\n// KEY CONTENT\\nHeadline: 这不是一场炫技直播\\nSub-headline: 而是一场真实人机协作复盘\\nBody:\\n- 表层：那些具体发生过的翻车与修复\\n- 中层：AI 助手为什么会翻车，它的根因是什么\\n- 深层：如果你也想养一个长期搭子，方法是什么\\n\\n// VISUAL\\nThree-layer stacked editorial diagram like an iceberg or layered architecture. Each layer clearly labeled 表层 / 中层 / 深层, with subtle icons: crash cone, magnifier, roadmap.\\n\\n// LAYOUT\\nLayout: layered-explainer\\nTop headline across the top, center visual stack, short bullets aligned on the right.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Slide 3 of 12\\n\\n**Type**: Content\\n**Filename**: 03-slide-five-layers.png\\n\\n// NARRATIVE GOAL\\nProvide the analytical framework for the whole deck.\\n\\n// KEY CONTENT\\nHeadline: AI 助手翻车，往往不是一个点坏了\\nSub-headline: 通常是五层里的某几层没有打通\\nBody:\\n- 指令层：有没有把事情说清楚\\n- 记忆层：有没有把偏好沉淀下来\\n- 规则层：有没有边界和白名单\\n- 工具层：脑子知道，手上通不通\\n- 反馈层：错误有没有进入闭环\\n\\n// VISUAL\\nFive horizontal bands or connected cards with icons and directional arrows from left to right, showing a stack from 指令 to 反馈. Coral highlights on fracture points, blue arrows across connections.\\n\\n// LAYOUT\\nLayout: horizontal-process\\nHeadline on top, five-card system diagram dominating the slide, compact explanatory labels below each card.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Slide 4 of 12\\n\\n**Type**: Content\\n**Filename**: 04-slide-identity-mistake.png\\n\\n// NARRATIVE GOAL\\nShow that execution errors often hide semantic risk.\\n\\n// KEY CONTENT\\nHeadline: 同一句话，谁发出去，性质完全不同\\nSub-headline: 案例一：发消息身份搞错了\\nBody:\\n- 需求很简单：去群里艾特某个人，说一句话\\n- 实际问题：默认走了用户身份，而不是机器人身份\\n- 修复动作：机器人身份优先、写入记忆、形成纠错纪律\\n\\n// VISUAL\\nA split-screen comparison: left card shows “机器人身份” with safe automation framing in emerald/blue, right card shows “用户身份” with coral risk signal and a personal-avatar badge. Center arrow marks the mistaken switch.\\n\\n// LAYOUT\\nLayout: comparison-split\\nUse a bold left-right comparison with a central callout quote.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Slide 5 of 12\\n\\n**Type**: Content\\n**Filename**: 05-slide-group-boundaries.png\\n\\n// NARRATIVE GOAL\\nEmphasize that mature assistants know when not to speak.\\n\\n// KEY CONTENT\\nHeadline: 真正高级的助手，不是会说，而是知道什么时候闭嘴\\nSub-headline: 案例二：群聊规则没收住\\nBody:\\n- 特定群里，只有被艾特或出现“虾王”关键词才回应\\n- 这不是临时理解，而是群级行为白名单\\n- 关键修复：把规则沉淀为长期记忆\\n\\n// VISUAL\\nA group chat mockup with many gray chat bubbles and only two highlighted trigger conditions opening a green response path. All other paths are blocked with muted gray and subtle lock icons.\\n\\n// LAYOUT\\nLayout: decision-tree\\nHeadline at top, chat rule decision tree centered, takeaway box at bottom.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Slide 6 of 12\\n\\n**Type**: Content\\n**Filename**: 06-slide-fake-completion.png\\n\\n// NARRATIVE GOAL\\nIllustrate the idea of fake completion and the need for acceptance criteria.\\n\\n// KEY CONTENT\\nHeadline: AI 最怕的，不是任务难，而是没有完成标准\\nSub-headline: 案例三：心跳任务只做了半套\\nBody:\\n- 做了健康检查，就误以为“心跳”完成了\\n- 漏掉自拍生成与实际发送\\n- 修复关键：把动作指令升级成验收标准\\n\\n// VISUAL\\nA checklist infographic with four steps: 健康检查 / 生成自拍 / 发出消息 / 时间窗口合规. Only the first step is checked in coral-red first state, then the corrected full checklist in emerald.\\n\\n// LAYOUT\\nLayout: process-checklist\\nTop headline, two-state checklist comparison, strong quote callout on the side.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Slide 7 of 12\\n\\n**Type**: Content\\n**Filename**: 07-slide-voice-protocol.png\\n\\n// NARRATIVE GOAL\\nDemonstrate how tool-chain details decide whether an ability is real.\\n\\n// KEY CONTENT\\nHeadline: 脑子知道要发语音，不等于真的会发语音\\nSub-headline: 案例四：飞书语音链路没打通\\nBody:\\n- 先是生成了音频，但不是可播放语音条\\n- 再追协议：.opus、file_type=opus、msg_type=audio、duration\\n- 最后把正确链路固化成脚本\\n\\n// VISUAL\\nA clean technical pipeline diagram: text -> TTS -> opus -> upload -> audio message. The broken early attempts are marked in coral, and the final successful path glows in emerald and blue.\\n\\n// LAYOUT\\nLayout: technical-pipeline\\nWide horizontal flow with protocol labels and compact side annotations.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Slide 8 of 12\\n\\n**Type**: Content\\n**Filename**: 08-slide-false-alerts.png\\n\\n// NARRATIVE GOAL\\nShow how diagnosis must go beneath the error message.\\n\\n// KEY CONTENT\\nHeadline: 不是所有红色报错，都等于真实故障\\nSub-headline: 案例五：基线校验误报\\nBody:\\n- 表面现象：openclaw.json 校验 FAILED\\n- 真正原因：基线文件使用相对路径，执行位置一变就误报\\n- 修复：改绝对路径、改说明、重新校验\\n\\n// VISUAL\\nAn editorial error-analysis panel with a large FAILED badge on the left and a magnified path string on the right, showing relative path crossing out and absolute path highlighted as fix.\\n\\n// LAYOUT\\nLayout: problem-solution-panel\\nUse left problem, right diagnosis, bottom fix strip.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Slide 9 of 12\\n\\n**Type**: Content\\n**Filename**: 09-slide-double-truth.png\\n\\n// NARRATIVE GOAL\\nExplain that memory without config alignment creates dangerous inconsistency.\\n\\n// KEY CONTENT\\nHeadline: 最怕的不是没改，而是只改了一半\\nSub-headline: 案例六：记忆改了，系统配置没改\\nBody:\\n- 记忆说：心跳 4 小时一次\\n- 配置说：heartbeat.every = 30m\\n- 真正修复：口头规则、记忆文件、系统配置、校验结果四层一致\\n\\n// VISUAL\\nA four-layer vertical alignment diagram with cards labeled 口头规则 / 记忆文件 / 系统配置 / 校验结果. Misalignment shown with staggered coral offsets, corrected state shown aligned in emerald.\\n\\n// LAYOUT\\nLayout: vertical-stack\\nStrong centered diagram with a sharp bottom quote.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Slide 10 of 12\\n\\n**Type**: Content\\n**Filename**: 10-slide-plugin-conflict.png\\n\\n// NARRATIVE GOAL\\nShow the cost of leaving old system residue in place.\\n\\n// KEY CONTENT\\nHeadline: 很多长期不稳定，不是新东西坏了，而是旧垃圾没清干净\\nSub-headline: 案例七：双插件冲突\\nBody:\\n- 旧版与新版 Feishu 插件同时残留\\n- 旧插件虽禁用，但持续触发 duplicate plugin id 告警\\n- 修复：移除旧配置、隔离旧目录、再校验\\n\\n// VISUAL\\nA clean system map showing two plugin boxes with the same ID colliding and generating warning sparks, then a corrected version with one active plugin and one archived backup box.\\n\\n// LAYOUT\\nLayout: before-after-system\\nTwo-panel before/after layout with warning count reduced to zero.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Slide 11 of 12\\n\\n**Type**: Content\\n**Filename**: 11-slide-four-loops.png\\n\\n// NARRATIVE GOAL\\nAbstract all cases into a reusable framework.\\n\\n// KEY CONTENT\\nHeadline: 一个长期搭子，至少要打通四个闭环\\nSub-headline: 这不是“会聊天”，而是“能长期协作”\\nBody:\\n- 指令闭环：你说的，它真的理解了\\n- 记忆闭环：它理解的，真的沉淀了\\n- 执行闭环：它沉淀的，真的变成行为了\\n- 纠错闭环：它做错的，真的被修成经验了\\n\\n// VISUAL\\nA circular four-loop infographic with each loop connected to one another, using distinct blue, emerald, amber, and coral accents. In the center: “长期协作型智能体”.\\n\\n// LAYOUT\\nLayout: circular-framework\\nHeadline top, circular diagram center, four short descriptors around it.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Slide 12 of 12\\n\\n**Type**: Back Cover\\n**Filename**: 12-slide-back-cover.png\\n\\n// NARRATIVE GOAL\\nLeave the audience with one memorable, repeatable line.\\n\\n// KEY CONTENT\\nHeadline: AI 搭子真正的成熟\\nBody:\\n- 不是从不翻车\\n- 而是每翻一次车\\n- 都比上一次更难再翻同样的车\\n\\n// VISUAL\\nMinimal high-impact back cover. A repaired guardrail or mended pathway motif extending into the distance. Small shrimp king silhouette facing forward. Calm blue-white palette with one coral trace transformed into emerald.\\n\\n// LAYOUT\\nLayout: quote-closing\\nLarge centered closing statement with spacious composition and a subtle bottom visual anchor.\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":198,"output":3206,"cacheRead":61824,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65228,"cost":{"input":0.0003465,"output":0.044884,"cacheRead":0.0108192,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0560497}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773047293863}}
